section#options
	h2 Options

	p
		strong P.S.&nbsp;

		|string/boolean config options can also be supplied using data attributes, e.g. data-min-date, data-default-date, data-date-format etc.
		br

		strong P.P.S&nbsp;
		span.dim this doesn't work in IE9 and IE10, unless you&nbsp;
		a.dim(target="_blank", rel="nofollow", href="https://www.npmjs.com/package/element-dataset") polyfill
		|.

	table.options
		thead
			tr
				th Config Option
				th Type
				th Default
				th Description
		tbody
			tr
				td altFormat
				td string
				td &quot;F j, Y&quot;
				td Exactly the same as date format, but for the altInput field
			tr
				td altInput
				td Boolean
				td false
				td
					| Show the user a readable date (as per altFormat), but return something totally different to the server.
			tr
				td altInputClass
				td String
				td &quot;&quot;
				td
					| This class will be added to the input element created by the altInput option.
					|&nbsp;Note that&nbsp;
					code altInput
					|&nbsp;already inherits classes from the original input.
			tr
				td allowInput
				td boolean
				td false
				td
					| Allows the user to enter a date directly input the input field. By default, direct entry is disabled.

			tr
				td appendTo
				td HTMLElement
				td null
				td
					| Instead of&nbsp;
					code body
					|, appends the calendar to the specified node instead.

			tr
				td clickOpens
				td boolean
				td true
				td
					| Whether clicking on the input should open the picker.
					| You could disable this if you wish to open the calendar manually with
					code .open()
			tr
				td dateFormat
				td string
				td &quot;Y-m-d&quot;
				td
					| A string of characters which are used to define how the date will be displayed in the input box. The supported characters are defined in the table below.
			tr
				td defaultDate
				td string/Date
				td null
				td
					| Set the initial selected date. Same as preloading a date string into an input&apos;s value attribute, but can also handle a Date object.
			tr
				td disable
				td array
				td []
				td See&nbsp;
					a(href="#disable") Disabling dates

			tr
				td disableMobile
				td Boolean
				td false
				td
					|Set&nbsp;
					code disableMobile
					|&nbsp;to true to always use the non-native picker.
					br
					| By default, Flatpickr utilizes native datetime widgets unless certain options (e.g. disable) are used.

			tr
				td enable
				td array
				td []
				td See&nbsp;
					a(href="#enable") Enabling dates

			tr
				td enableTime
				td boolean
				td false
				td Enables time picker
			tr
				td enableSeconds
				td boolean
				td false
				td Enables seconds in the time picker.

			tr
				td hourIncrement
				td integer
				td 1
				td Adjusts the step for the hour input (incl. scrolling)

			tr
				td inline
				td boolean
				td false
				td Displays the calendar inline

			tr
				td maxDate
				td String/Date
				td null
				td The maximum date that a user can pick to (inclusive).

			tr
				td minDate
				td String/Date
				td null
				td The minimum date that a user can start picking from (inclusive).


			tr
				td minuteIncrement
				td integer
				td 5
				td Adjusts the step for the minute input (incl. scrolling)

			tr
				td mode
				td String
				td "single"
				td
					code "single"
					|,&nbsp;
					code "multiple"
					|, or&nbsp;
					code "range"

			tr
				td nextArrow
				td string
				td
					code &gt;
				td HTML for the arrow icon, used to switch months.

			tr
				td noCalendar
				td boolean
				td false
				td Hides the day selection in calendar.
					br
					|Use it along with&nbsp;
					code enableTime
					|&nbsp;to create a time picker.

			tr
				td onChange
				td function, [functions]
				td null
				td Function(s) to trigger on every date selection. See&nbsp;
					a(href="#eventsAPI") Events API

			tr
				td onClose
				td function, [functions]
				td null
				td Function(s) to trigger on every time the calendar is closed. See&nbsp;
					a(href="#eventsAPI") Events API

			tr
				td onOpen
				td function, [functions]
				td null
				td Function(s) to trigger on every time the calendar is opened. See&nbsp;
					a(href="#eventsAPI") Events API

			tr
				td onReady
				td function, [functions]
				td null
				td Function to trigger when the calendar is ready. See&nbsp;
					a(href="#eventsAPI") Events API


			tr
				td parseDate
				td function
				td false
				td Function that expects a date string and must return a Date object

			tr
				td prevArrow
				td string
				td
					code &lt;
				td HTML for the left arrow icon.

			tr
				td shorthandCurrentMonth
				td boolean
				td false
				td Show the month using the shorthand version (ie, Sep instead of September).

			tr
				td static
				td boolean
				td false
				td
					| Position the calendar inside the wrapper and next to the input element. (Leave
					code false
					| unless you know what you&apos;re doing.

			tr
				td time_24hr
				td boolean
				td false
				td Displays time picker in 24 hour mode without AM/PM selection when enabled.

			tr
				td utc
				td boolean
				td false
				td
					| When true, dates will parsed, formatted, and displayed in UTC. It&apos;s recommended that date strings contain the timezone, but not necessary.

			tr
				td weekNumbers
				td boolean
				td false
				td Enables display of week numbers in calendar.

			tr
				td wrap
				td Boolean
				td false
				td
					a(href='https://chmln.github.io/flatpickr/#example-strap') Custom elements and input groups
